WEBVTT

00:02.000 --> 00:04.440
Ms Bello claims the affair
happened four years ago,

00:04.440 --> 00:06.160
while the MP was visiting Nigeria.

00:06.160 --> 00:08.680
Those are the guys
I saw getting into the grey van.

00:08.680 --> 00:11.320
To tell you the truth, I'd rather
avoid this place altogether.

00:11.320 --> 00:14.320
Not easy when half your clients
are in the same building.

00:14.320 --> 00:17.120
Actually, Mr Knox,
I came to ask for your help.

00:17.120 --> 00:18.800
I see.

00:18.800 --> 00:20.160
The mask.

00:20.160 --> 00:22.040
Control to Kilo 1.

00:22.040 --> 00:25.360
Gemma, Operation Vanguard is
compromised.

00:25.360 --> 00:26.920
The seventh floor is down.

00:26.920 --> 00:28.560
Vanguard needs a new home.

00:28.560 --> 00:30.880
You accuse me of sabotage, and...

00:30.880 --> 00:32.480
..and now you want my help.

00:32.480 --> 00:35.920
China's going to lose the facial-rec
bid. The US are waiting in line.

00:35.920 --> 00:39.440
We carry the same burdens.
Guilt and regret.

00:39.440 --> 00:41.280
If you want to give yourself
the best chance,

00:41.280 --> 00:42.560
you'll free yourself of them.

00:42.560 --> 00:43.920
In an exclusive interview,

00:43.920 --> 00:46.680
we speak to Victoria Bello
from her home in Lagos.

00:46.680 --> 00:49.400
This isn't about facial rec -
this is about me.

00:49.400 --> 00:51.720
I beg your pardon, Mr Turner?
I said, I hope you're proud,

00:51.720 --> 00:53.400
forcing my family away
from their home.

00:53.400 --> 00:54.840
He looks like you.

00:54.840 --> 00:57.280
What? Victoria Bello's son, Amandi.

00:57.280 --> 00:59.120
I've been looking at him.

00:59.120 --> 01:00.560
What are you talking about?

01:00.560 --> 01:02.520
Free Shaun? As in Shaun Emery?

01:04.720 --> 01:08.320
Your paternity test has come back
negative - you must be delighted.

01:08.320 --> 01:12.600
Why do you think she made those
claims? I understand.

01:12.600 --> 01:16.120
Some people will go to desperate
lengths to jump the queue.

01:16.120 --> 01:17.880
Mr Knox, do we have a match?

01:17.880 --> 01:19.320
Yes.

01:19.320 --> 01:21.040
Nikolai Mirsky.

01:22.280 --> 01:24.760
PHONE RINGS

01:22.280 --> 01:24.760
Hello?

01:24.760 --> 01:26.440
ISAAC: Hello, Isaac.

01:26.440 --> 01:28.400
DOOR BUZZER

01:28.400 --> 01:33.800
This programme contains some
violent scenes and strong language.

01:33.800 --> 01:35.440
DOOR BUZZER

01:36.800 --> 01:38.640
DOOR BUZZER

01:56.240 --> 02:00.680
REPEATED BUZZING

02:17.920 --> 02:19.520
Room service.

02:25.040 --> 02:27.800
What the fuck is going on?

02:27.800 --> 02:29.520
Isaac, Isaac,

02:29.520 --> 02:32.680
this place is rigged with cameras -
please don't do anything silly.

02:45.040 --> 02:47.160
This is nice at least.

02:48.160 --> 02:49.800
Presidential Suite.

02:50.840 --> 02:52.080
Apt.

02:54.080 --> 02:57.640
You, er, you might want
to put some clothes on.

02:58.880 --> 03:01.560
Start...talking.

03:01.560 --> 03:03.960
Yeah, I'm not supposed
to do that, mate.

03:03.960 --> 03:05.400
I'm just here to get you.

03:08.560 --> 03:12.080
To get me? Â£11 for pistachio nuts?
Are you having a laugh?

03:12.080 --> 03:15.760
So help me God, I will throttle you
with my bare hands.

03:15.760 --> 03:17.720
I don't care how many cameras
are watching.

03:17.720 --> 03:21.000
What the hell were you doing outside
my door pretending to be me?

03:22.720 --> 03:24.880
What? But... Pretending to...?

03:26.640 --> 03:29.720
I guess they're just, you know,
just trying to get in.

03:29.720 --> 03:31.880
Who? Who? Who's trying to get in?

03:31.880 --> 03:33.920
Look, I need you to know, mate,

03:33.920 --> 03:36.080
I honestly had no idea
this was going to happen.

03:36.080 --> 03:38.520
Aliza, she is completely
in the dark. I only found out

03:38.520 --> 03:41.480
the truth of it myself last night.
I haven't slept a bloody wink.

03:42.640 --> 03:45.720
You know, I would find it
a lot easier to open up

03:45.720 --> 03:47.360
to you if you unclenched your fists

03:47.360 --> 03:49.640
and stopped looking
like you're about to hit me.

03:54.520 --> 03:57.160
It's probably why they asked me
to get you.

03:57.160 --> 04:00.080
People look at me and think I can
handle myself, but the truth is

04:00.080 --> 04:02.160
I am a bloody coward.
Rhys, shut up. Shut up.

04:02.160 --> 04:04.400
Just SHUT UP and listen,

04:04.400 --> 04:06.400
cos I won't say this again.

04:06.400 --> 04:08.160
Who are THEY?

04:13.280 --> 04:15.080
Well...

05:03.320 --> 05:06.400
PHONE RINGS

05:18.600 --> 05:21.920
RINGING TONE
SHOWER RUNS

05:33.600 --> 05:35.320
Bathroom's free.

05:42.040 --> 05:44.880
SHOWER RUNS

05:55.840 --> 05:59.520
The real question here is did the
Home Office knowingly

05:59.520 --> 06:01.440
obstruct Victoria Bello's
application?

06:01.440 --> 06:03.160
Daddy!

06:03.160 --> 06:04.720
DOOR OPENS

06:04.720 --> 06:06.400
Yes!

06:06.400 --> 06:08.080
ISAAC CHUCKLES

06:08.080 --> 06:12.480
Oh, hello. Hello. I missed you.

06:14.760 --> 06:16.480
Hey.

06:16.480 --> 06:20.720
So, um, it's safe to come back home,

06:20.720 --> 06:25.000
whenever you're ready. There's
no press outside. It's all over.

06:25.000 --> 06:27.040
Are you coming home, Daddy?

06:27.040 --> 06:31.160
Um, well, Daddy has to go back
to London.

06:31.160 --> 06:35.320
But I'll be back as soon as I can.
Yeah? Go and get your things.

06:35.320 --> 06:36.920
Come on. Come on.

06:40.280 --> 06:42.920
So, you saw it? The result?

06:44.960 --> 06:47.560
I thought there wasn't
going to be a paternity test.

06:47.560 --> 06:50.000
You said they were going to fake
the results.

06:53.240 --> 06:55.800
It's the right result, Simmy.

06:57.440 --> 06:59.000
What's up?

07:00.480 --> 07:03.120
Well, if she was making it all up,

07:03.120 --> 07:05.920
why did the Home Office hold back
her application?

07:07.960 --> 07:10.680
That's exactly
what I intend to find out.

07:13.440 --> 07:14.720
Right?

07:41.640 --> 07:44.520
ELECTRONIC BEEPING AND WHIRRING

07:46.680 --> 07:49.720
TRAIN PASSES

08:02.720 --> 08:05.040
Make yourselves at home.

08:05.040 --> 08:07.800
The bottom floor's all yours.

08:07.800 --> 08:10.640
As long as you stay
in your allotted zones,

08:10.640 --> 08:13.080
everybody will get along just fine.

08:19.800 --> 08:23.280
You see the latest video release
of your protegee?

08:25.920 --> 08:27.680
You showed me.

08:28.720 --> 08:30.640
Last night? Mm.

08:30.640 --> 08:33.520
I'm talking about this morning.
We got the red flag.

08:33.520 --> 08:36.160
Don't you get updates
from Chelten Ham?

08:37.400 --> 08:38.960
Cheltenham.

08:40.320 --> 08:43.640
It's a bit like cereal,
only it's called Free Shaun.

08:43.640 --> 08:46.920
Or I might go more esoteric,
like The Bus Stop.

08:46.920 --> 08:48.600
What are you talking about?

08:48.600 --> 08:50.920
Free Shaun? As in Shaun Emery?

08:52.280 --> 08:54.800
What are you talking about?

08:54.800 --> 08:56.520
Free Shaun? As in Shaun Emery?

08:58.000 --> 09:00.200
She knows she's being watched.

09:03.320 --> 09:05.400
Nothing changes.

09:07.640 --> 09:09.520
We continue as planned.

09:12.360 --> 09:14.680
It's your rodeo now.

09:25.440 --> 09:28.120
RINGING TONE

09:29.400 --> 09:31.760
PHONE RINGS

09:50.320 --> 09:52.680
RINGING CONTINUES

09:56.200 --> 09:59.520
Did you obstruct Victoria Bello's
application, Mr Turner? Is this

09:59.520 --> 10:01.480
a crisis for the Home Office,
Mr Turner?

10:01.480 --> 10:03.440
Mr Turner,
do you believe the media now?

10:03.440 --> 10:04.600
No hoodie today, Zac?

10:04.600 --> 10:07.320
I have every faith
in the Home Secretary.

10:07.320 --> 10:09.800
He has my full support. Thank you.

10:09.800 --> 10:12.320
SHOUTING

10:30.000 --> 10:33.360
"Every faith in the Home Sec"?
What are you up to?

10:33.360 --> 10:35.880
Where is Gill today?
I'm not his private secretary.

10:35.880 --> 10:39.440
But you are on the server, aren't
you? How are you enjoying policy,

10:39.440 --> 10:42.120
by the way? I only ask cos you spend
most of your time

10:42.120 --> 10:43.920
seemingly checking my numbers.

10:43.920 --> 10:46.200
Which are spiking higher than ever,
by the way.

10:46.200 --> 10:48.640
Congrats on that. So, what's this?

10:48.640 --> 10:51.400
The old band back together again?
What goes on tour

10:51.400 --> 10:53.760
and all that jazz? Cos I'm in.
If you'll have me,

10:53.760 --> 10:56.160
whack out the old...

10:53.760 --> 10:56.160
IMITATES ELECTRIC GUITAR

10:56.160 --> 10:57.520
Rhys, could you...?

10:57.520 --> 11:00.560
I was just asking Aliza
why she's been tracking my stats.

11:00.560 --> 11:02.400
Good question.

11:02.400 --> 11:04.600
What do you expect?
I've always been Team Zac.

11:04.600 --> 11:08.280
To be fair, that is true. Even when
I was fired, you answered my calls.

11:08.280 --> 11:11.360
I tried you - it wouldn't go
through. Yeah. Fucking Vodafone.

11:11.360 --> 11:13.680
But then again,
maybe it was just a decoy

11:13.680 --> 11:16.440
to avoid doing what I actually asked
you to do, which was to dig up

11:16.440 --> 11:19.200
Victoria Bello's paperwork
and check for concerns.

11:19.200 --> 11:21.920
I thought that part of the story
would just...go away.

11:21.920 --> 11:24.160
The front page news?
Yeah, in The Guardian.

11:24.160 --> 11:26.760
Everyone else has gone
with "Lying Bitch", essentially.

11:26.760 --> 11:29.720
Anyway, none of it seems
to be doing you any harm.

11:29.720 --> 11:32.320
Aliza, there's going to be
an inquiry

11:32.320 --> 11:35.240
and none of us are safe.
If the Home Secretary himself had

11:35.240 --> 11:37.720
a hand in obstructing
Bello's application,

11:37.720 --> 11:40.680
it's going to come out.
So, if you know anything,

11:40.680 --> 11:43.000
Aliza, you need to share it.

12:03.360 --> 12:05.240
I've been calling you all day.

12:05.240 --> 12:07.840
I-I-I've been in Salford, so...

12:07.840 --> 12:10.160
I saw you.

12:10.160 --> 12:12.280
BBC Breakfast.

12:12.280 --> 12:13.920
I assume that was you?

12:13.920 --> 12:16.800
Yes. So, look, I'm just on my way
to see the Home Secretary, so...

12:16.800 --> 12:19.600
On your way to becoming Home Sec,
according to Twitter.

12:20.760 --> 12:22.520
I need to speak to you.

12:37.040 --> 12:40.000
Gregory Knox came through.
The unmasking.

12:42.160 --> 12:45.800
We have a name. Nikolai Mirsky.

12:45.800 --> 12:47.880
Russian ex-military.

12:47.880 --> 12:50.320
I know. We need to get this to SO15.

12:50.320 --> 12:54.080
Except I can't explain how I came by
it, so I suggest it comes from you.

12:55.040 --> 12:58.000
Me? At the time of the attack,
you were Security Minister.

12:58.000 --> 13:00.200
You had clearance
to any number of operations.

13:00.200 --> 13:03.200
All you need to do is say
you can't reveal the source.

13:03.200 --> 13:04.960
I-I-I don't know.

13:04.960 --> 13:07.840
It sounds a bit like faking evidence
to me.

13:09.320 --> 13:10.880
What?

13:10.880 --> 13:12.840
You've taken the footage,
manipulated it,

13:12.840 --> 13:14.800
now you want to hide where it
came from.

13:14.800 --> 13:17.480
For use as intelligence,
not evidence.

13:17.480 --> 13:20.400
HE SCOFFS
Now you sound like a true believer.

13:20.400 --> 13:23.840
This is a visual on
a Russian state-sanctioned killer.

13:23.840 --> 13:26.960
We need to act.
We're the only ones that have it.

13:26.960 --> 13:28.720
ISAAC SIGHS

13:28.720 --> 13:31.320
Look, I know we have other battles.

13:31.320 --> 13:34.040
But we can't expose Correction
while we're under attack by

13:34.040 --> 13:37.000
a foreign power.
We need to win this one first.

13:42.440 --> 13:44.600
Khadija heard your recording.

13:45.960 --> 13:48.480
The Home Secretary
discussing Correction.

13:48.480 --> 13:51.760
You mean Khadija Khan,
who interviewed Victoria Bello

13:51.760 --> 13:54.120
and claimed the Home Office
obstructed her application?

13:54.120 --> 13:56.960
Isaac, the deal is still intact.

14:06.960 --> 14:08.520
What deal?

14:19.120 --> 14:20.800
Somebody got to you.

14:22.240 --> 14:25.680
Didn't they? I don't know
what you're talking about.

14:25.680 --> 14:27.280
Jesus Christ! I'm not recording!

14:27.280 --> 14:30.240
I'm sorry, Detective, but I think
I've given you enough of my time.

14:30.240 --> 14:32.840
You can talk to me, Isaac. You can
trust me. Don't lie to me!

14:36.360 --> 14:39.240
You really think
I need to take this shit from you?

14:43.560 --> 14:47.520
You know how I know it was
you...on BBC Breakfast

14:47.520 --> 14:48.920
and not your deep-fake?

14:51.040 --> 14:52.720
You touched your cross.

14:55.880 --> 14:58.880
You run your thumb over the cross on
your neck chain when you're anxious.

14:58.880 --> 15:01.560
No, I don't.
It's my job to notice things.

15:02.920 --> 15:06.560
Your deep-fake's never done that.
Only you.

15:11.880 --> 15:13.320
You're all right, Isaac.

15:14.960 --> 15:18.640
Not that kind of politician,
like you said.

15:18.640 --> 15:20.280
Whatever's happened,

15:20.280 --> 15:23.120
whatever they've threatened you
with, I can help you.

15:24.400 --> 15:26.160
We can get through this.

15:30.880 --> 15:34.120
Who was it?! Who got to you?!

15:35.120 --> 15:37.600
Garland? The Home Secretary? Who?

15:39.680 --> 15:42.600
You have a case to solve.
I have a job to do.

15:42.600 --> 15:44.480
Other battles, like you said.

15:45.600 --> 15:49.280
So why don't we just get on with
it and go our separate ways?

16:08.920 --> 16:11.400
PHONE VIBRATES

16:13.360 --> 16:18.160
Carey. Ma'am. I thought you'd
like to know, comms are back up.

16:18.160 --> 16:20.040
We're rolling out new units
to all ops.

16:20.040 --> 16:22.000
What about the camera network?

16:22.000 --> 16:24.360
Secure. Vanguard has a new base.

16:24.360 --> 16:26.440
Or I could bring the comms to you?

16:26.440 --> 16:28.640
That is...if you're back at work?

16:33.880 --> 16:36.280
Meet me in an hour.
Where do you want me, ma'am?

16:36.280 --> 16:39.720
Broadcasting House,
three o'clock, sharp. Yes, ma'am.

16:47.240 --> 16:50.160
Thanks to the intervention
of our US partners,

16:50.160 --> 16:52.600
Operation Vanguard is now secure.

16:53.640 --> 16:56.000
Vladimir Putin himself
couldn't compromise it.

16:56.000 --> 16:57.520
CHUCKLING

16:57.520 --> 17:01.280
Although this remains
a UK counterterrorism operation,

17:01.280 --> 17:05.200
inside this building
you are in US territory,

17:05.200 --> 17:07.960
and you will operate in accordance
with US laws,

17:07.960 --> 17:11.240
regulations,
and standard operating procedures.

17:11.240 --> 17:13.600
Our hosts will be on hand at
all times

17:13.600 --> 17:17.760
to support us through
any, uh, cultural differences.

17:19.040 --> 17:20.960
Connor here will be leading a
support team

17:20.960 --> 17:23.840
of technical operatives, alongside
someone many of you will be

17:23.840 --> 17:26.200
acquainted with already,
our very own DI Phillips,

17:26.200 --> 17:28.520
who's been on secondment here
for the past six months,

17:28.520 --> 17:31.200
and I'm pleased to say
hasn't picked up the accent.

17:31.200 --> 17:33.200
CHUCKLING

17:33.200 --> 17:36.600
Um, I know you're all
still reeling from

17:36.600 --> 17:42.120
the tragic loss
of Detective Sergeant Patrick Flynn,

17:42.120 --> 17:44.840
Specialist Firearms Officer
Jason McKenna

17:44.840 --> 17:47.200
and Specialist Firearms Officer
Lee Bradbury.

17:48.320 --> 17:53.280
But the way to...honour
our fallen colleagues...

17:55.320 --> 17:58.800
..is to catch the scum
that took their lives.

18:01.800 --> 18:03.480
Thank you, sir.

18:04.840 --> 18:06.120
As Commander Hart said...

18:06.120 --> 18:09.280
Is he going to maintain
his stiff upper lip?

18:09.280 --> 18:11.160
I think I see it quivering.

18:12.800 --> 18:14.080
..with a much wider range

18:14.080 --> 18:16.360
of intelligence-gathering tools
at our disposal.

18:16.360 --> 18:17.760
Now, given the urgency,

18:17.760 --> 18:20.680
we've begun analysing existing data
from the operation,

18:20.680 --> 18:22.920
and we've uncovered
a few truffles already.

18:26.120 --> 18:27.800
Danny? Sir?

18:32.480 --> 18:35.160
A long time since
you called me that.

18:36.360 --> 18:38.240
I just wanted to say thank you.

18:40.280 --> 18:42.480
That was the team talk
we all needed.

18:42.480 --> 18:44.600
It's the last one
you'll hear me give.

18:46.040 --> 18:48.520
I stopped by the Commissioner's
office this morning.

18:48.520 --> 18:51.320
Handed in my 7-28.
You're resigning?

18:51.320 --> 18:53.240
After Vanguard, I'm out.

18:56.760 --> 18:58.880
Don't worry, Gemma.

18:58.880 --> 19:00.960
I didn't give the real reason.

19:13.040 --> 19:15.960
I'm in the middle of a meeting.
I've got about two minutes.

19:15.960 --> 19:17.840
Did you have to interview her?

19:17.840 --> 19:19.120
I beg your pardon?

19:19.120 --> 19:21.800
Victoria Bello.
Was that really necessary?

19:21.800 --> 19:23.720
SHE SCOFFS

19:21.800 --> 19:23.720
Last time I checked,

19:23.720 --> 19:26.400
I'm not required
to justify my editorial choices

19:26.400 --> 19:29.400
to the authorities. We're not living
in a police state yet.

19:29.400 --> 19:32.560
Well, I hope it was worth it. Cos
Isaac Turner is now out of the deal.

19:32.560 --> 19:34.440
What, because of that? Oh, please.

19:34.440 --> 19:38.320
You do not understand. I understand
perfectly. I will call Zac myself,

19:38.320 --> 19:40.320
show the requisite humility.

19:40.320 --> 19:43.040
It's a dance.
You'd do well to learn the steps.

19:43.040 --> 19:45.440
Learn this!
I was with Isaac Turner an hour ago.

19:45.440 --> 19:48.120
He wouldn't even admit we had a
deal! He doesn't trust us,

19:48.120 --> 19:51.520
and that is your fault.
Lower your tone.

19:51.520 --> 19:54.240
I don't let anyone raise their voice
at me off camera.

19:54.240 --> 19:56.880
I am not anyone!
You have fucked it up, Khadija.

19:56.880 --> 19:58.360
For all of us!

20:04.480 --> 20:06.240
I thought we said three o'clock?

20:06.240 --> 20:08.200
I'd rather be early - always.

20:09.680 --> 20:11.160
How much did you hear?

20:12.280 --> 20:13.680
Nothing.

20:14.720 --> 20:16.960
I brought your comms.

20:16.960 --> 20:20.040
And I thought you'd
want to know there's a new lead.

20:22.000 --> 20:24.360
Take me to the new base.
I'll follow.

20:28.520 --> 20:29.880
After the presentation,

20:29.880 --> 20:32.720
the Home Secretary will make
what he promises will be

20:32.720 --> 20:34.400
a short announcement,

20:34.400 --> 20:37.720
and the Security Minister will take
questions from the press.

20:37.720 --> 20:40.280
APPLAUSE

20:43.120 --> 20:46.920
Britain's border security
will soon be bolstered

20:46.920 --> 20:49.440
by a digital layer of protection,

20:49.440 --> 20:53.120
provided by a company
who count among their clients

20:53.120 --> 20:54.640
the US Pentagon.

20:54.640 --> 20:57.200
All of us who value the security

20:57.200 --> 20:59.760
and sovereignty of our nation

20:59.760 --> 21:04.520
will value the support
of Clear Horizons AI. Thank you.

21:04.520 --> 21:07.240
Care to make a statement about
Victoria Bello? Have you spoken

21:07.240 --> 21:09.440
to Isaac Turner today, Home
Secretary? Did anyone

21:09.440 --> 21:10.640
at the Home Office obstruct

21:10.640 --> 21:13.280
Victoria Bello's application,
Home Secretary? Thank you.

21:43.520 --> 21:45.200
This is where the magic happens.

21:45.200 --> 21:48.600
Tom. What have I missed?
Lots, by the looks of things.

21:48.600 --> 21:50.800
Well, that's what comes of skipping
the briefings.

21:50.800 --> 21:52.800
We can't hold the class up
just for you, Carey.

21:52.800 --> 21:55.680
I've been on compassionate leave,
so...

21:55.680 --> 21:57.080
..be compassionate.

21:57.080 --> 21:59.880
No time for compassion.
Not in the middle of a manhunt.

22:10.120 --> 22:11.680
Who's the target?

22:11.680 --> 22:15.000
A Russian National. Nikolai Mirsky.

22:16.440 --> 22:19.880
We've got every facial-rec system
in the UK looking for him

22:19.880 --> 22:22.360
and every ANPR looking
for his van.

22:24.800 --> 22:28.120
Do we, um, do we know the source?

22:28.120 --> 22:30.400
I mean, how did he get on our
radar?

22:30.400 --> 22:32.120
You think they'd tell me?

22:35.600 --> 22:37.040
How are you feeling, Rachel?

22:37.040 --> 22:39.440
Ma'am. Just getting up to speed.

22:39.440 --> 22:41.960
I appreciate you coming back
to work so soon,

22:41.960 --> 22:43.760
after the experience you've had.

22:43.760 --> 22:46.800
I'd rather...keep going.

22:46.800 --> 22:48.480
Rest when you're dead.

22:49.560 --> 22:51.440
Can I show you something?

22:59.320 --> 23:03.120
Frank, I felt DCI Carey should be
briefed on the ongoing developments.

23:04.920 --> 23:06.480
Welcome to America.

23:10.280 --> 23:12.120
Is that...? The hospital.

23:12.120 --> 23:15.200
Staff entrance.
The night of DS Flynn's murder.

23:15.200 --> 23:18.840
I thought whoever did this took over
the camera network completely?

23:21.080 --> 23:25.000
This section of the briefing
is sensitive.

23:25.000 --> 23:26.440
Understood.

23:27.800 --> 23:31.840
Every state has its own style
when it comes to subterfuge.

23:31.840 --> 23:33.680
Its own telltale signs.

23:33.680 --> 23:36.920
The Russians, for instance,
very sloppy. Online and off.

23:36.920 --> 23:40.480
They hacked SO15, but it appears
they didn't consider our...

23:42.120 --> 23:43.720
..auxiliary network.

23:43.720 --> 23:45.760
You can access the real footage?

23:45.760 --> 23:47.280
We can recover it

23:47.280 --> 23:50.480
from a covert signal
embedded in the time code.

23:50.480 --> 23:53.400
It's kind of like scratching
the oil paint off a canvas

23:53.400 --> 23:55.640
to reveal the pencil drawing
underneath.

23:55.640 --> 23:58.480
Stop me if I'm...getting too
technical.

24:02.000 --> 24:04.560
So, de-correction, then?

24:08.840 --> 24:12.600
Eventually we'll recover
all the footage from the attack.

24:12.600 --> 24:18.000
But, for now, our focus,
Todd, is this.

24:19.160 --> 24:20.960
Nikolai Mirsky.

24:25.000 --> 24:27.960
I-I thought Isaac Turner's
witness statement said

24:27.960 --> 24:30.720
the killers were
wearing face masks.

24:30.720 --> 24:32.800
Like I said, sloppy.

24:34.760 --> 24:37.960
Result. Intelligence on the suspect
is patchy.

24:37.960 --> 24:41.760
Facial rec points us to
a private security firm in Belarus.

24:41.760 --> 24:44.880
Russian black ops,
by any other name.

24:44.880 --> 24:47.400
Do we know if the suspect's
still in the UK?

24:47.400 --> 24:50.520
They hacked the feeds at Heathrow
last time - they could do it again.

24:50.520 --> 24:52.240
The manhunt is under way, Rachel.

24:53.240 --> 24:55.240
I'd like you to run something else.

24:55.240 --> 24:59.080
DC Tan is briefed
and making progress,

24:59.080 --> 25:04.040
but this requires the leadership
of someone fully conversant.

25:04.040 --> 25:05.640
What does, ma'am?

25:05.640 --> 25:07.760
The criminal case
against the suspect.

25:07.760 --> 25:10.400
We need an evidence dossier,

25:10.400 --> 25:13.400
robust enough to put in front of
a judge.

25:13.400 --> 25:19.040
The more evidence we can compile
against Nikolai Mirsky the better.

25:21.640 --> 25:23.040
Understood.

25:31.440 --> 25:33.280
You know the way back.

25:43.000 --> 25:46.240
I appreciate the chance to speak,
Home Secretary.

25:46.240 --> 25:48.080
I imagine you can guess what this
is about.

25:48.080 --> 25:51.640
Uh, well, let me see. You told BBC
Breakfast I failed to deliver.

25:51.640 --> 25:54.040
You told reporters I have
your full support.

25:54.040 --> 25:57.360
So, at a push, I'd guess you were
trying to steal my fucking job?

25:57.360 --> 26:00.120
So, I should have said
you don't have my support?

26:00.120 --> 26:02.760
You'll be saying the department
needs a breath of fresh air next.

26:02.760 --> 26:04.240
You're fucking me over, Isaac.

26:04.240 --> 26:06.680
Have the decency to look me
in the eye while you're doing it.

26:06.680 --> 26:08.840
You can hardly blame me for leaving
the department

26:08.840 --> 26:10.360
acutely aware of its shortcomings.

26:10.360 --> 26:13.080
Not to mention our unkept promise
of firm but fair immigration.

26:13.080 --> 26:14.920
Oh, don't quote the manifesto at me.

26:14.920 --> 26:17.240
You weren't even elected
when we wrote that.

26:20.520 --> 26:22.520
After all I've done for you.

26:24.160 --> 26:25.680
Go on.

26:26.720 --> 26:29.320
No, what did you do for me,
Home Secretary?

26:31.000 --> 26:32.880
Take a wild guess.

26:34.240 --> 26:37.120
I mean, I thought I was selected for
government by the PM?

26:38.240 --> 26:42.920
But if you had a hand in making me
Security Minister, Home Secretary...

26:42.920 --> 26:45.840
I'm not talking about making
you a minister.

26:45.840 --> 26:47.320
So, what are you talking about?

26:47.320 --> 26:49.360
I'm talking about that girl.

26:50.360 --> 26:52.000
Victoria Bello?

26:52.000 --> 26:54.880
Unless you have others
that I don't know about?

26:54.880 --> 26:56.680
I told you, that was all lies.

26:56.680 --> 26:58.720
You told me that a few days ago.

26:58.720 --> 27:01.560
That application hit my desk
six months back.

27:01.560 --> 27:05.080
Sorry, hit your desk? Why yours?

27:05.080 --> 27:07.720
Why don't you ask
your private secretary?

27:07.720 --> 27:09.160
Aliza?

27:09.160 --> 27:10.680
She came to you?

27:10.680 --> 27:13.200
Yep. All flummoxed,
convinced it was real,

27:13.200 --> 27:15.600
convinced that love child was yours,

27:15.600 --> 27:19.120
and convinced, as I was, that
it would be the bloody ruin of you.

27:19.120 --> 27:20.920
And then, so you...?

27:23.880 --> 27:26.720
The file found its way
to the bottom of the pile.

27:26.720 --> 27:30.200
Got lost. Drowned in a sea of
bureaucracy.

27:32.040 --> 27:33.680
You're welcome.

27:36.280 --> 27:38.400
So, that's how it's done, is it?

27:39.800 --> 27:42.000
And all that
because you assumed it was true.

27:42.000 --> 27:45.720
Don't be so bloody supercilious.
Are you really that surprised?

27:46.840 --> 27:49.800
No, Home Secretary,
I'm not surprised. In fact,

27:49.800 --> 27:52.120
it's exactly what I thought.

27:52.120 --> 27:54.680
I just needed to hear you say it.

27:55.960 --> 27:58.760
What do you mean? To say what?
What are you talking about?

27:58.760 --> 28:01.320
Don't walk away from me.
Don't you...!

28:02.560 --> 28:05.680
What is that?!
Are you recording this?!

28:05.680 --> 28:09.080
Are you mad?! Recording the Home
Secretary without his consent!

28:09.080 --> 28:11.160
That is a breach
of national security!

28:11.160 --> 28:12.560
I will have you stripped

28:12.560 --> 28:15.600
of every clearance level there is,
you little prick.

28:17.200 --> 28:20.880
It's insurance, Rowan,
in case you try to deny it.

28:20.880 --> 28:22.640
Deny it?! What are you talking
about?!

28:22.640 --> 28:25.720
Why are you doing this to me,
Isaac?!

28:27.920 --> 28:30.240
It's nothing personal.

28:40.360 --> 28:42.680
QUIET CHATTER

29:10.400 --> 29:13.520
Is it possible to embed a video
in time code?

29:13.520 --> 29:16.160
You don't do small talk,
do you, Carey?

29:16.160 --> 29:18.760
How's your day going, Tom?
Not bad. How's yours?

29:18.760 --> 29:19.960
Good.

29:19.960 --> 29:22.320
Is it possible to embed a video
in time code?

29:22.320 --> 29:25.680
I think you mean a time code signal
in audio, don't you?

29:25.680 --> 29:27.680
Nope. I mean what I said.

29:27.680 --> 29:29.760
Well, then,
you're talking bollocks.

29:29.760 --> 29:32.520
That's your technical assessment,
is it?

29:32.520 --> 29:33.760
Yep.

29:35.000 --> 29:38.440
I don't suppose it's possible
to recover a signal

29:38.440 --> 29:40.680
from a hacked feed either, is it?

29:40.680 --> 29:46.120
Like scratching the paint off
a canvas to reveal the drawing.

29:47.240 --> 29:48.800
What are you talking about?

29:50.480 --> 29:51.880
Nothing.

30:12.600 --> 30:15.600
Ma'am. The suspect's name was used
to rent

30:15.600 --> 30:18.560
a storage unit in Clapham two years
ago. It might be a dead end -

30:18.560 --> 30:20.800
the storage company is
no longer in business,

30:20.800 --> 30:23.280
but do you want me to head down
there and take a look?

30:24.680 --> 30:27.640
No, you stay here. I'll go.
Yes, ma'am.

30:38.160 --> 30:40.360
PHONE VIBRATES

30:41.520 --> 30:43.640
Hello? It's me.

30:43.640 --> 30:46.680
What phone are you calling from?
Have you left yet?

30:46.680 --> 30:50.480
Yeah. Just now.
I'm right here. Why?

30:50.480 --> 30:52.880
Good. I need you to do something
for me.

30:52.880 --> 30:55.600
Look, in the bathroom,
there's a laptop.

31:06.520 --> 31:07.880
Hi.

31:10.360 --> 31:12.640
You guarantee
they won't print my name?

31:12.640 --> 31:16.440
The clue is in the word anonymous.
Anonymous whistle-blower.

31:41.800 --> 31:44.440
I'm afraid you've caught me
on the hoof.

31:44.440 --> 31:46.640
Train was delayed
coming back from my conference,

31:46.640 --> 31:48.840
and now I'm running late for
a dinner engagement.

31:48.840 --> 31:52.600
I always seem to catch you either
coming or going. Time and tide.

31:52.600 --> 31:55.840
Was that the Home Secretary's
conference? His big announcement?

31:55.840 --> 31:58.160
Er, no. Different one.

31:59.520 --> 32:03.200
They're here, aren't they?
Clear Horizons AI?

32:04.600 --> 32:07.720
Yes, on the top floor.
US company, right?

32:07.720 --> 32:09.760
Silicon Valley, of course.

32:09.760 --> 32:13.160
But now they're taking over
the world, so to speak.

32:14.440 --> 32:16.040
You must be delighted.

32:17.200 --> 32:20.680
Your client winning the
UK facial recognition contract.

32:20.680 --> 32:23.200
You mentioned half your clients were
in this building.

32:23.200 --> 32:25.760
I'm assuming that includes them.

32:25.760 --> 32:29.240
We don't get involved
with their commercial operations.

32:32.800 --> 32:35.000
What do you get involved in?

32:37.640 --> 32:39.840
I'm sorry, Detective,
but where's this going?

32:39.840 --> 32:42.040
Surely you can see the problem,
Mr Knox.

32:43.440 --> 32:46.480
You belong to an independent
advisory group.

32:46.480 --> 32:50.880
You advised the government against
doing business with a Chinese firm,

32:50.880 --> 32:53.640
whilst in the pocket
of their US rivals.

32:55.440 --> 32:58.200
Looks like a conflict of interests
to me.

32:58.200 --> 33:00.720
I assure you,
I'm not in anyone's pocket.

33:04.200 --> 33:07.320
Tell me, what is it you do here,
exactly?

33:09.200 --> 33:14.080
Your website mentions
political consultancy,

33:14.080 --> 33:16.000
data analysis.

33:16.000 --> 33:18.800
Sounds...vague.

33:19.920 --> 33:22.560
I'd be glad to educate you,
Detective, but as I mentioned...

33:22.560 --> 33:24.840
Half the social media companies
on the planet seem

33:24.840 --> 33:28.920
to have an office in this building.
That's a lot of data to analyse.

33:28.920 --> 33:31.400
But as I mentioned,
I don't have all evening.

33:33.400 --> 33:37.600
How did you unmask the suspect
exactly? Nikolai Mirsky?

33:37.600 --> 33:41.120
Well, you supplied the image.
You know which program we used.

33:41.120 --> 33:43.440
Show me the process,
the working out.

33:43.440 --> 33:46.880
That involves my technical team,
none of whom are here.

33:46.880 --> 33:48.480
It's after hours.

33:48.480 --> 33:51.200
Did you supply the image
to anyone outside this company?

33:51.200 --> 33:53.320
You were quite clear about that.

33:53.320 --> 33:56.200
See, you haven't actually answered
the question.

33:56.200 --> 33:59.160
Is that something you teach
your politicians?

33:59.160 --> 34:00.880
Am I under suspicion, Detective?

34:00.880 --> 34:02.760
Increasingly.

34:02.760 --> 34:04.280
Well, if you want to arrest me

34:04.280 --> 34:07.200
for a conflict of interest,
go ahead.

34:08.240 --> 34:10.080
That won't be the charge.

34:23.720 --> 34:27.480
Suspect vehicle. Golf, X-ray,
six, six, Alpha, Echo Echo.

34:27.480 --> 34:30.000
Pos ID. Coleman Street, Echo,
Charlie, four.

34:30.000 --> 34:32.840
Vehicle heading north.
Bring it up. Let's see it.

34:32.840 --> 34:36.720
Deploy armed units to the vicinity.
Prepare for tactical response.

34:38.040 --> 34:41.040
The murder of Edison Yao and the
attempt on your life were designed

34:41.040 --> 34:43.640
to send Isaac Turner
into police protection,

34:43.640 --> 34:46.360
to keep him out of the public eye.
That's when this began.

34:46.360 --> 34:50.840
What began? The onslaught
of disinformation and lies

34:50.840 --> 34:54.040
that led us to believe
we were under attack from China,

34:54.040 --> 34:58.840
that ended with UK facial
recognition being handed to America.

34:58.840 --> 35:01.160
You have completely lost me.

35:03.680 --> 35:05.360
I don't believe you.

35:07.280 --> 35:10.120
I'm not continuing this conversation
until I have a lawyer.

35:10.120 --> 35:13.120
What is it you don't want me
to see on that laptop, Mr Knox?

35:13.120 --> 35:14.520
What?

35:14.520 --> 35:16.960
You've been glancing at it
like a schoolboy who forgot

35:16.960 --> 35:20.000
to delete his search history.
This is ridiculous.

35:23.800 --> 35:25.480
SIREN BLARES

35:26.640 --> 35:27.920
I can produce a warrant

35:27.920 --> 35:30.600
to seize every computer
in this building within 20 minutes.

35:30.600 --> 35:31.840
I'm afraid I've kept my dinner

35:31.840 --> 35:33.640
companions waiting....
But at this point,

35:33.640 --> 35:36.560
failure to cooperate will force my
hand. I employ corporate lawyers,

35:36.560 --> 35:39.400
but not criminal ones, so I'd like
time to arrange representation.

35:39.400 --> 35:42.000
Take one more step, and I will
have no option but to arrest.

35:43.040 --> 35:46.000
Gregory Knox, I am arresting you
for obstructing a police officer

35:46.000 --> 35:48.440
in the execution of their duty.
You do not have to say...

35:48.440 --> 35:49.800
Where the fuck are you going?!

35:49.800 --> 35:53.080
Do NOT make me add resisting
arrest to the list of charges!

35:55.400 --> 35:56.800
Do not move.

36:01.240 --> 36:04.040
Kilo 3 to all units.
Request urgent backup...

36:04.040 --> 36:06.200
RACHEL'S VOICE: All clear,
all clear.

36:08.880 --> 36:11.280
SHE GROANS

36:22.720 --> 36:25.240
BEEPING

36:31.760 --> 36:34.640
I hope you don't think of me
too unfavourably, Detective.

36:36.320 --> 36:37.960
I'm not a violent person.

36:39.000 --> 36:42.360
I've certainly never laid a finger
on a woman, as they say.

36:42.360 --> 36:44.480
Present company excepted, of course.

36:45.720 --> 36:51.280
Point is, I share the widely held
public-facing belief

36:51.280 --> 36:54.280
that violence towards women
is abhorrent.

36:54.280 --> 36:57.320
I say public-facing because online
it's a different picture.

36:57.320 --> 36:59.120
You poll 100 university students -

36:59.120 --> 37:01.720
"Is violence towards women
ever justified?" -

37:01.720 --> 37:03.440
You'll get 100 emphatic noes.

37:03.440 --> 37:04.920
But look at their Twitter feeds -

37:04.920 --> 37:07.440
you'll find 10% to 15% have,

37:07.440 --> 37:10.720
at some point or another,
sent death threats to women.

37:10.720 --> 37:13.560
Just one of the countless incidences
of data providing

37:13.560 --> 37:16.800
a clearer look at human behaviour
than humans themselves.

37:21.440 --> 37:22.840
Ugh!

37:28.000 --> 37:31.320
Suspect vehicle, check.
A501, Moorgate, north.

37:31.320 --> 37:35.640
Lima Unit. Two minutes.
A501, City Road, south.

37:35.640 --> 37:39.200
Mike Unit.
Two minutes. A5201, east.

37:39.200 --> 37:40.960
Copy that.

37:40.960 --> 37:43.800
SIREN BLARES

37:43.800 --> 37:45.800
Just like old times.

37:49.560 --> 37:53.280
Gregory Knox, I am arresting you for
conspiracy to murder,

37:53.280 --> 37:56.640
perverting the course of justice,
grievous bodily harm,

37:56.640 --> 37:59.320
assaulting a police officer
and resisting arrest.

38:01.000 --> 38:05.720
Suspect vehicle turning west.
Ropemaker Street. Out of range.

38:05.720 --> 38:07.320
Oh, no, stay on him!

38:07.320 --> 38:09.480
Repeat, out of range.
Blind spot, 50m.

38:09.480 --> 38:11.600
I want every border feed
where I can see it.

38:11.600 --> 38:15.000
And I want every armed unit in
London deployed to that vicinity.

38:31.440 --> 38:33.000
CLICKING

38:33.000 --> 38:35.560
SHE GROANS

38:38.400 --> 38:39.760
Agh!

38:48.560 --> 38:50.320
What is this?

38:54.080 --> 38:56.080
If I were you, Detective Carey...

38:58.840 --> 39:00.640
..I'd run.

39:27.760 --> 39:31.000
Where's your phone?

39:31.000 --> 39:33.640
Where's your phone?
Where is it?!

40:07.920 --> 40:09.760
TABLET BEEPS

40:43.800 --> 40:45.480
Ugh!

40:46.680 --> 40:48.800
This terminal is not in service.

40:52.840 --> 40:55.240
LIFT DINGS

40:52.840 --> 40:55.240
Doors opening.

41:22.280 --> 41:24.600
This terminal is not in service.

41:24.600 --> 41:28.200
Proceed to car H, to the left rear.

41:36.800 --> 41:39.440
LIFT DINGS

41:36.800 --> 41:39.440
Doors opening.

41:47.680 --> 41:49.960
BEEPING

42:41.560 --> 42:43.680
PANICKED BREATHING

42:49.160 --> 42:53.600
Shots fired. Shots fired.
Target down. Target down.

42:54.920 --> 42:57.440
Shots fired. Threat neutralised.

42:57.440 --> 43:00.000
Target down. Repeat. Target down.

44:06.960 --> 44:08.720
HE CLEARS HIS THROAT

44:37.160 --> 44:40.560
KHADIJA ON TV: "Nothing to see
here," says Rowan Gill.

44:40.560 --> 44:43.080
But an anonymous Home Office
whistle-blower claims

44:43.080 --> 44:46.120
Gill had direct involvement in
the interference

44:46.120 --> 44:48.400
of British passport applications,

44:48.400 --> 44:51.320
including that of Victoria
Bello's.

44:51.320 --> 44:54.960
So, can he cling on
and endure another scandal?

44:54.960 --> 44:57.960
Or is the Home Secretary losing
his grip?

44:57.960 --> 45:00.080
Thank you.

45:00.080 --> 45:02.720
CLAMOUR

45:02.720 --> 45:04.880
MUSIC: Theme from Newsnight

45:06.280 --> 45:08.400
PHONE VIBRATES

45:19.040 --> 45:21.600
PHONE BUZZES
DOOR BUZZER

45:23.920 --> 45:25.640
PHONE BUZZES
DOOR BUZZER

45:25.640 --> 45:29.880
Rhys, shut up. Shut up. And listen!
Because I won't say this again.

45:31.640 --> 45:33.920
Who are they?

45:38.560 --> 45:40.240
Well,

45:40.240 --> 45:43.240
you know our...consultants.

45:44.640 --> 45:47.960
Our c... What, Gregory's lot? Truro?

45:47.960 --> 45:50.120
I mean, we did consider
several alternatives.

45:50.120 --> 45:52.720
As I recall, you were the one
who made the final decision.

45:52.720 --> 45:55.200
We hired them a year ago.
What's the problem with them?

45:55.200 --> 45:57.560
Not to be pedantic,
but we didn't hire them, did we?

45:57.560 --> 45:59.240
They offered their services
for free.

45:59.240 --> 46:01.880
Which, now I think about it,
should've raised some alarm bells.

46:01.880 --> 46:04.720
I thought they just crunched data
and helped us reach voters?

46:04.720 --> 46:06.240
It's more the way they do it.

46:09.400 --> 46:12.760
I mean, it's bloody clever.
They are the dons of data.

46:12.760 --> 46:15.680
You can't blame yourself
for wanting to work with them.

46:15.680 --> 46:17.400
Truro Analytics?

46:17.400 --> 46:20.440
They're the ones who've been trying
to destroy me? All this time?

46:22.120 --> 46:25.280
They, er, haven't been trying
to destroy you, mate.

46:25.280 --> 46:27.760
Well, what the fuck have they
been doing?

46:29.080 --> 46:30.920
You really ought to get dressed.

46:30.920 --> 46:33.080
They, er, want to show you
something.

46:35.360 --> 46:37.600
I'm supposed to take you down,

46:37.600 --> 46:39.720
er, stairs. Sorry, that was...

46:42.160 --> 46:44.680
Why? What the fuck's downstairs?

46:44.680 --> 46:47.640
As I understand it,

46:47.640 --> 46:49.560
some sort of conference.

46:53.360 --> 46:56.200
MUSIC: Breath Of Fresh Air
by Clement Marfo

46:56.200 --> 46:58.680
# I've seen faces
Lifted weights up off the floor

46:58.680 --> 47:00.400
# I've had highs and I've had lows

47:00.400 --> 47:02.640
# I've got business I ain't closed

47:02.640 --> 47:05.000
# I've read pages
I've got words to say

